[3] Pakistan (Sindh): 3 new cases
Date: Sat 23 Nov 2019
Source: Urdu Point [edited]
https://www.urdupoint.com/en/health/dg-health-confirms-3-new-polio-cases-in-sindh-769518.html


Director general [DG] health Masood Ahmed Solangi has confirmed that 3 new cases of polio have surfaced in Sindh.

He said here on Saturday [23 Nov 2019] that 3 children, aged between 30 months and 12 years, in Karachi, Shaheed Benazirabad, and Jamshoro districts had been diagnosed positive with polio. With the 3 new cases in Sindh, the total in the ongoing year [2019] had reached 13, he said.

According to the DG, the polio victims included a 12-year-old and an 8-month-old child in Karachi; [a 3-year-old girl] belonging to Union Council 2 in Sakrand, Shaheed Benazirabad; and a 30-month-old [girl] of UC Nango Line in Kotri, Jamshoro.

He said that the children belonging to Karachi and Shaheed Benazirabad received more than 7 doses of polio immunization during as many supplementary immunization activities (SIA). The details were not available as to whether SIA doses were received by [the girl] of Jamshoro district, he added.

[Byline: Sumaira FH]

