[In the past 2 days there have been a total of 7 newly confirmed cases reported from Pakistan: 3 in Sindh province and 4 in Khyber Pakhtunkhwa province. While both provinces have seen polio activity, the 2 most recently reported cases in Pakistan from Upper and Lower Kohistan are the 1st cases reported from these areas during 2019, signifying continued spread of the virus to new districts. The addition of these 7 newly confirmed cases will bring the total number of WPV1-associated cases reported from Pakistan with dates of onset this year (2019) to 93. In addition, there have been 9 cVDPV2-associated cases with date of onset in 2019 as well.

A good map showing districts and provinces of Pakistan can be found at https://reliefweb.int/sites/reliefweb.int/files/resources/pak215_pakistan_districts_v5_a0_20181203.pdf. Kohistan is located in the northeast of the country sharing a border with the Pakistani-administered Kashmir.

As for the ongoing outbreak of cVDPV2 in the southern Mindanao region of the Philippines, the above report provided more details on the geographic locations of the cases and the suboptimal vaccination histories of the 3 newly confirmed cases.

A map showing the provinces of the Philippines can be found at https://www.mapsofworld.com/philippines/philippines-political-map.html. - Mod.MPP]
